Post_ID: 2738598863668467326 | Post_Code: CYBdSgjP1Z- | Likes: 91 | Caption: .<\br>蔬食味噌豆乳鍋<\br><\br>這些年來，不時進出樹林。見過林林總總人類活動對郊野的衝擊，野生動植物的生境大受破壞，時常思考如何取得平衡。上完山野不留痕環境保育導師課程，解答了自己許多疑問。無何否認，山的確有自我修復的能力，但面對香港的流量，是否足以應付呢？<\br><\br>洗碗水也要用樽帶走？看似太瘋狂，原因離不開山野無痕的信念。山野無痕絕非金科玉律、教條主義，外國做法與香港做法亦有少許不同，如何處理並沒有最好的答案，以下可作參考：<\br><\br>•預早計劃行程，處理食材。在家中除去不必要的部分，拆去包裝紙清洗分類回收，食材分餐入袋，從而減少帶上山的垃圾。（可以使用矽膠食物袋、食物盒、蜜蠟紙、可重用保鮮袋等，煮食後可當作垃圾袋，帶回家再清洗）<\br><\br>•餐單設計時可考慮少/無油、少醬汁、不會留下湯汁的食物，以方便清潔。（例如一鍋到底、無水料理等）<\br><\br>•避免煮氣味濃烈的食物、露營時將食物、廚餘掛高，減少被動物的騷擾。鼠類、野豬等動物喜歡晚間或清晨期間覓食，這些做法可保障野生動物的習性不被改變。<\br><\br>•食材預備時切忌眼濶肚窄。若擔心不夠食，可以準備乾糧，即使用不著也可以帶回家，或者帶個大食朋友包底。🤫<\br><\br>•多選擇植物性食材，動物性食材比植物性食材更難清潔，動物性食材大多含有豐富油脂，需花費更多清潔用品清潔。<\br><\br>•煮食後將廚具用廚房紙抹乾淨，帶回家再清潔，減少用水，面對水源不足的營地更加適用。<\br><\br>•茶籽粉/茶包/橙皮/檸檬皮/柑皮屬天然有效去油的清潔物，當中茶籽粉、茶包需使用熱水輔助。<\br><\br>食物的味道固然重要，過份追求會淪為苦行，難以持久。<\br><\br>__________________________________________________<\br><\br>#camping #hkcamping #hkwildlife #campinglife #camper #campingfood #outdoors #outdoorfood #mountainlife #香港露營 #露營 #野營 #野營料理 #野炊 #料理 #山料理 #露營食譜 #露營食 #山野無痕 #levaenotrace #lnt #蔬食 #素食 #蔬食食譜 #素食食譜 #messtin #豆乳鍋 | Tags: ['#camping', '#hkcamping', '#hkwildlife', '#campinglife', '#camper', '#campingfood', '#outdoors', '#outdoorfood', '#mountainlife', '#香港露營', '#露營', '#野營', '#野營料理', '#野炊', '#料理', '#山料理', '#露營食譜', '#露營食', '#山野無痕', '#levaenotrace', '#lnt', '#蔬食', '#素食', '#蔬食食譜', '#素食食譜', '#messtin', '#豆乳鍋'] | Time Stamp: 1640686446

de tristeza y desmotivación. <\br><\br>La persona que se ve afectada pierde el interés en realizar tareas cotidianas e, incluso, aquellas actividades que con anterioridad disfrutaba.<\br><\br>La al aislamiento social. <\br><\br>Desde un punto de vista espiritual, la depresión puede originarse debido a un trauma emocional que afecta a la capacidad del globo energético de regular la energía o, incluso, a conflictos kármicos que están aún por resolver. <\br><\br>La TERAPIA CUÁNTICA considera que son los traumas emocionales y kármicos aquellos que influyen directamente en la salud del ser Post_ID: 2737979256854572913 | Post_Code: CX_QaCvNG9x | Likes: 82 | Caption: This is Silvey Brice "S.B." Vaughters, who farm still stands as one of the last remaining dairy landscapes in once-rural DeKalb County. Now simply known as "Vaughters' Farm," the meadow and barn off of Klondike Road were once a small part of a massive patchwork of farms that stretched across the county, forming the dairy capital of Georgia. As suburban sprawl grew out of Atlanta over the course of the 20th Century, Vaughters didn't want to see his farm turned into a subdivision. Post_ID: 2735921597790966217 | Post_Code: CX38jKZplHJ | Likes: 413 | Caption: Everybody wants to reach the peak, but there is no growth on the top of a mountain. It is in the valley that we slog through, the lush grass and rich soil, learning and becoming what enables us to summit life’s next peak.<\br>-Andy Andrews<\br><\br>I think that climbing mountains is like a therapy to me in a way that I can directly relate the climb to my journey through life.&nbsp; Whether it be romantic relationships, family/friends or your career.&nbsp; It all directly correlates with one another. <\br><\br>At the beginning as you're making your way along your approach, you're full of excitement, anticipation and fear of what's to come.. slogging through the valleys, through the bush, the ups and downs it takes, until you get a solid feel for the adventure ahead.&nbsp; You don't give up because it gets tough for a minute.. you fight through it, you show you're dedicated and committed to to the process, to reaching that summit.&nbsp; Just as you're getting to know you're journey, falling in love with that beaten path ahead of you - it finally comes into view, you see the big picture, you see what you really signed up for... and then it hits you like a bag of bricks. You realize damn this is a big objective with alot of risk!&nbsp; At this point in time you're left with 2 choices.. your fight or flight response kicks in, adrenaline starts pumping, body starts releasing serotonin and you wonder wtf you're doing here, is this really what you want to do!?&nbsp; For me.. if I've had the mental clarity to get myself into this position, then that answer is always yes!&nbsp; Staring that mountain in the face, absolutely terrified, absolutely humbled and ready to give it everything I have!! Theres no better feeling!&nbsp; From that point forward you're free! You send it with everything that you have! You might slip once in a while, but what's important is that you never give up on the things or people that you love,&nbsp; the things you're dedicated too, because if you turn around and run when that fight or flight response kicks in.. you'll always be left wondering what if.. <\br><\br>F**k regrets<\br>Climb that damn mountain<\br>Make that career jump<\br>Shoot your shot with that boy/girl<\br>Love your friends and family | Tags: [] | Time Stamp: 1640367291

Post_ID: 2735903655851563312 | Post_Code: CX34eEquZkw | Likes: 236 | Caption: Are you making new hiking or travel plans for the new year? <\br><\br>There are seven Leave No Trace that you need to know before you hit the trails.  It’s more than just packing out your trash. <\br><\br>Save for future reference. <\br><\br>1.  Plan Ahead and Prepare<\br>This is really about your safety.  Learn about the trail an its conditions so you are properly prepared with what you need and the appropriate to finish your route.  No one wants to spend the night out in the wilderness unless they were planning on camping.<\br><\br>2.Travel and Camp on Durable Surfaces<\br>Stay on the trails to protect vegetation and cryptobiotic soil. Don’t create side trails to avoid mud.  If you are traveling cross country, make sure you stick to rock or dry washes to minimize your impact.<\br><\br>3.Dispose of Waste Properly<\br>This includes packing out all your trash and following local regulations about disposal of TP and poop.<\br><\br>4.Leave it as you found it. <\br>Rock cairns look fun but unofficial cairns can confuse hikers leading them off a trail and no one wants to get lost out in the wilderness.<\br><\br>5.  Minimize Campfire Impact.<\br>This means only using a fire when necessary and only if local regulations allow.<\br><\br>6. Respect Wildlife. <\br>Give the animals plenty of space and educate yourself about how to handle an encounter.  Ask yourself, Do I know the difference of how to handle an encounter with a bear or a mountain lion?<\br><\br>7. Be Considerate of Others. <\br>This is just all around important in everyday life. Uphill hikers have the right of way.  Keep you noise level low and pets under your control.<\br><\br>When I first started hiking I just thought leave no trace meant pack out may trace and don’t take anything form the trail . <\br><\br>Comment below something new you learned or didn’t know as a new hiker.<\br><\br>#hikingtrails #optoutside #leavenotrace #werehikers #lnt #outdoorlovers #greenriver | Tags: ['#hikingtrails', '#optoutside', '#leavenotrace', '#werehikers', '#lnt', '#outdoorlovers', '#greenriver'] | Time Stamp: 1640365152

Post_ID: 2735171068346972387 | Post_Code: CX1R5hYvzjj | Likes: 287 | Caption: Sold <\br>Tatsuzo Shimaoka (1919-2007) Inlaid Rope (Zogan) Technique Yunomi Meoto Pair - Living National Treaure Mashiko Pottery<\br>The cups do not bear the mark which tells that they were made before 1974 when Shimaoka began singing his works.<\br><\br>Tatsuzo Shimaoka was a Japanese mingei potter who studied under Shoji Hamada and later became the second Living National Treasure of Mashiko in Japan. He was best known for his unique Jomon Zogan style of pottery, and was a master of many slip decorating and firing techniques for pottery. Throughout his career Shimaoka San worked collaboratively with a group of workers, students, and apprentices from Japan and abroad.<\br><\br>Width 8cm and 9cm<\br>Height 8cm and 9cm<\br><\br>Condition<\br>Unused work made in 1960-1970s.<\br>No chips. Post_ID: 2734923062647456296 | Post_Code: CX0ZgkFIAIo | Likes: 14 | Caption: Un anciano conoce a un joven quien le pregunta: <\br>- ¿Se acuerda de mí?<\br>Y anciano dice que no. <\br>Entonces el joven dice que fue su alumno. <\br>Y el profesor pregunta:<\br>- ¿Qué estás haciendo?<\br>- Soy profesor <\br>- Ah que bueno ¿Como yo?<\br>- Sí. Me convertí en maestro porque usted me inspiró a ser también como usted.<\br>Luego le pregunta al tipo cuándo lo inspiró a ser maestro. Y el alumno cuenta la historia:<\br>“Un día, un amigo mío, también estudiante, llegó con un hermoso reloj nuevo, y decidí que lo quería para mí y lo robé, lo saqué de su bolsillo. Poco después, mi amigo notó el robo y se quejó a usted (maestro). Entonces se dirigió a la clase:<\br>- El reloj de su colega fue robado. Quien lo robó, que lo devuelva.<\br>No lo devolví porque no quería hacerlo. <\br>Luego cerró usted la puerta y le dijo a todos que se pusieran de pie y que iría a uno por uno para buscar en los bolsillos de todos hasta encontrar el reloj. Pero les dijo a todos que cerraran los ojos, que haría esto con los estudiantes con los ojos cerrados ...<\br>Todos cerraron los ojos y usted fue de bolsillo en bolsillo y cuando llegó al mío encontró el reloj y lo tomó. Continuó usted buscando en todos, y cuando terminó, dijo: 'Abran los ojos. Ya tenemos el reloj'.<\br>No me dijo usted nada. <\br>Nunca mencionó el episodio. <\br>Nunca dijo quién había robado a nadie."<\br>Y ese día, usted salvó mi dignidad para siempre. Fue el día más vergonzoso de mi vida. Pero también el fue el día que mi dignidad se salvó de no convertirme en ladrón, mala persona, etc. Nunca dijo nada. <\br>No me dio apenas una lección moral. Y recibí el mensaje. Y entendí, que esto es lo que debe hacer un verdadero educador.<\br> ¿Se acuerda de ese episodio, maestro?<\br>Y el profesor responde:<\br>- Recuerdo la situación, el reloj robado, busqué en todos, etc. <\br>Pero no te recordaba. <\br>Porque también cerré los ojos mientras buscaba.<\br><\br>(Esto es la esencia de la docencia).<\br><\br>Si Para Corregir Necesitas Humillar... no sabes enseñar!...<\br><\br> Tomado del muro de Rosa López Casaña<\br>#nievessuarez #constelacionesfamiliares#tenerife #eneagrama#biogestal #LNT #lanuevaterapia #energía | Tags: ['#nievessuarez', '#constelacionesfamiliares', '#tenerife', '#eneagrama', '#biogestal', '#LNT', '#lanuevaterapia', '#energía'] | Time Stamp: 1640248256

Post_ID: 2733827862455908224 | Post_Code: CXwgfTav_eA | Likes: 85 | Caption: If a Moab elopement is in your future, you’ve probably started to wonder what exactly you need to gear up for your big day!⁠<\br>⁠<\br>Here are a few essentials I highly recommend packing in your adventure bag…⁠<\br>⁠<\br>• A good pair of hiking shoes or boots. Thick hiking socks & liners are also encouraged.⁠<\br>• A wedding dress you can move around in. You don’t want something that is too form-fitting that will restrict your movements or activities. ⁠<\br>• A suit that isn’t too restrictive. Suits, like dresses, can at times be restrictive, so make sure you don’t split your pants moving around!⁠<\br>• Plenty of water. Moab is dry & at high elevation. You’ll want to be sure to drink lots of water & be sure to eat!  I love my Hydroflask water bottle because it is big & keeps my water cold. Camelbacks are another good option as they hold a lot of water! Don’t forget the snacks!⁠<\br>• Have a copy of your permit. Most places in Moab require you to carry a physical copy of your permit, make sure you don’t leave home without yours.⁠<\br>⁠<\br>Keep in mind you are NOT allowed to have rice, birdseed, confetti, or any non-native plant seed, this also means no seeded bouquets during your elopement. Post_ID: 2733613668013195260 | Post_Code: CXvvyXTFD_8 | Likes: 115 | Caption: The Lone Toilet!  Every day on Highway 37, just west of Vallejo, thousands of people drive by an old outhouse in the middle of a marsh. This is the strange story of how it got there. Just a warning if you want to visit, this is a very hard place to get here. Photographer Pedro Garcia and I had to use a boat to get to the out house. I was nominated for an Emmy with this story. Post_ID: 2733306451100901395 | Post_Code: CXup7xQJyAT | Likes: 12 | Caption: 📖末日生存手冊📖<\br><\br>近十年來，台灣山火起因中，「山區活動用火不慎」此因素高達17.30%，僅次於農墾引火不慎。而我們要如何在登山時，避免因野炊等活動而引發森林大火呢？<\br><\br>台灣在2007年由林務局引入LNT 7大原則（Leave No Trace的縮寫），意為無痕山林或無痕戶外，也被稱之為環境最小衝擊法則。<\br><\br>1. 事前充分的規劃與準備<\br>2. 在可承受地點行走宿營<\br>3. 適當維護環境處理垃圾<\br>4. 勿取走任何資源與物件<\br>5. 減低用火對環境的衝擊<\br>6. 保育自然環境與野生物<\br>7. 尊重其他的山林使用者<\br><\br>其中第五點「注意野外用火」中包含：<\br>1️⃣盡量使用便攜爐具煮食和營燈照明。<\br>2️⃣如果迫不得已要生火，首先要確認在你所待的地方生火是否合法、有無引發森林大火的可能。<\br>3️⃣之後清出防火圈，儘量生小火，不砍樹只取用地上的小樹枝。<\br>4️⃣最後將木炭燒成灰燼，澆滅營火，分散冷卻的灰燼。<\br><\br>🔥登山爐：登山客在進行戶外活動時，除了野炊生火還更多選擇，近年來許多廠商推出了專業的登山爐具🥘，能夠遠離地面、架高生火烹煮食材，避免有引發森林大火的風險。<\br><\br>為了保護和珍惜環境，將傷害發生的機會降到最低，每個人都該在出發前進大自然前，檢視是否徹底的準備好對環境最有利的器具，同時遵守LNT 7大原則，做好與自然和諧共處的決心！<\br><\br>資料來源：Tina outdoor、The SOTO WindMaster<\br><\br>#末日未生🕊️ #森林大火 #登山 #登山爐具 #LNT | Tags: ['#末日未生🕊️', '#森林大火', '#登山', '#登山爐具', '#LNT'] | Time Stamp: 1640055541

Post_ID: 2733123267156707907 | Post_Code: CXuASF6OwpD | Likes: 73 | Caption: Is it worth it to hire a specialized elopement photographer?⁠ ⁠<\br>⁠<\br>⁠The answer to this question comes down to what type of elopement you are having. We have extensive knowledge of the outdoors & are well prepared for fast-changing weather conditions with backup plans in place. We can assist with creating a day-of timeline & provide you with the best times to elope in specific locations throughout the year. We care deeply about the environment, practice #leavenotrace & know how to act around wildlife safely. We do in-depth location scouting to find you an ideal spot for your dream elopement, a very time-consuming task. We can recommend other vendors in the industry & fun ideas to make your day unique. We help with a marriage license, special use permits, & coordinating your day. ⁠<\br>⁠<\br>We don't take what we do lightly, & we believe that your elopement (still your wedding day) deserves so much more than a few quick photos.⁠<\br>⁠<\br>I personally think that a specialized elopement photographer is definitely worth the investment when it comes to an adventure elopement. ⁠Your wedding day is a big deal, & you deserve the guidance & knowledge of a photographer who will treat it as such. ⁠<\br>⁠<\br>If you're interested in taking an in-depth look at all the planning services I provide for my couples, be sure to check out my blog post 'Hiring an Elopement Photographer vs. Hiring a Photographer for Your Elopement'. Post_ID: 2733024428255785615 | Post_Code: CXtpzzAprKP | Likes: 36 | Caption: On this chilly Monday morning, we're looking back on warmer and more temperate times from the 2021 Gold Butte National Monument project. <\br>.<\br>This dedicated group of volunteers spent the week pulling invasive tamarisk, closing up social trails, and closing up illegal ATV trails. Gold Butte National Monument is found in southeastern Nevada and covers nearly 300,000 acres of remote, rugged desert landscape. Here you'll discover vibrant chiseled red sandstone, mesmerizing canyons, and mountains that contrast desolate stretches of the Mojave Desert. Gold Butte National Monument is home to Nevada’s first designated Backcountry Byway<\br>.<\br>The area is popular for outdoor recreation, and visitors to the monument can hike to rock art sites, drive the Gold Butte Backcountry Byway to the area’s namesake mining ghost town, hunt desert bighorn sheep, or tour the area’s peaks and canyons on horseback.<\br>.<\br>We’re looking forward to our return in 2022 😎 If you visit, respect this beautiful public land and leave no trace.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>#wildernessvolunteers #givingsomethingback #wv2021GoldButteNationalMonument #stewardship #conservation #GoldButte #nationalmonument #backcountrybyway #bureauoflandmanagement #blm #tamariskremoval #tamarisk #invasive #nevada #leavenotrace #lnt #trailmaintenance #petroglyphs #petroglyphpanels #mojavedesert  #volunteer #hiking #whitneypocket #friendsofgoldbutte #littlefinland #devilsthroat #virginpeak | Tags: ['#wildernessvolunteers', '#givingsomethingback', '#wv2021GoldButteNationalMonument', '#stewardship', '#conservation', '#GoldButte', '#nationalmonument', '#backcountrybyway', '#bureauoflandmanagement', '#blm', '#tamariskremoval', '#tamarisk', '#invasive', '#nevada', '#leavenotrace', '#lnt', '#trailmaintenance', '#petroglyphs', '#petroglyphpanels', '#mojavedesert', '#volunteer', '#hiking', '#whitneypocket', '#friendsofgoldbutte', '#littlefinland', '#devilsthroat', '#virginpeak'] | Time Stamp: 1640021922

Both dispersed camping and open ground fires are strictly prohibited on park lands. <\br><\br>If you would like to sleep under stars in Hot Springs National Park, we encourage you to take advantage of the amenities that the Gulpha Gorge Campground has to offer. Post_ID: 2732823825518181941 | Post_Code: CXs8MpJvD41 | Likes: 8 | Caption: Como realizar um levantamento de necessidade de treinamento? 😳<\br><\br>O Levantamento de Necessidades de Treinamento (LNT) nada mais é que um conjunto de estratégias e ações para identificar quais os colaboradores e equipes precisam de capacitação e qual treinamentos são indicados para cada um deles.<\br><\br>Não há dúvidas de que com treinamentos eficazes, os colaboradores se desenvolvem e executam melhor o seu papel dentro da empresa.<\br><\br>Por isso a importância do LNT, com a sua utilização fica mais fácil para o RH, determinar metas de curto, médio e longo prazos, de forma mais eficaz, reduzindo gastos que não levarão a resultado algum se forem agir no achismo.<\br><\br>Quando o LNT já é aplicado no processo de onboarding, é possível mapear as hard e soft skills do novo colaborador e, assim, entender se ele precisa passar por treinamentos específicos para que possa ter um melhor desempenho no cargo.<\br><\br>Quando utilizado na avaliação de desempenho, é possível identificar e analisar se os colaboradores aproveitaram os treinamentos oferecidos, aprimoraram suas habilidades e se desenvolveram novas competências.<\br><\br>O LNT é mesmo uma ferramenta indispensável para o RH e para a empresa.<\br><\br>E você, como você escolhe seus treinamentos? Post_ID: 2732369251748184196 | Post_Code: CXrU1uVpoCE | Likes: 41 | Caption: H I P E R T I R O I D I S M O o tiroides hiperactiva es una afección consistente en una mayor producción de la hormona tiroidea por la glándula tiroides.<\br><\br>Esta glándula produce las hormonas que regulan cómo las células emplean la energía en el cuerpo, más conocido como metabolismo. Por ello, es considerada uno de los órganos más importantes del sistema endocrino.<\br><\br>SÍNTOMAS ➠ Ansiedad, nerviosismo, inquietud, frecuencia cardíaca acelerada, problemas del sueño, pérdida de peso, aumento del sudor, pérdida del cabello, cansancio, dificultad para concentrarse, intolerancia al calor, aumento del apetito, entre otros.<\br><\br>ꕥ REMEDIOS NATURALES PARA EL HIPERTIROIDISMO con bebidas matinales caseras:<\br><\br>- Jugo de rábano y limón para inhibir la secreción de hormona tiroidea.<\br>- Infusión de menta y melisa para regular los nervios y disminuir la actividad de la glándula tiroides.<\br>- Jugo de fresa y durazno para reducir la absorción de yodo.<\br><\br>¿Cómo la TERAPIA CUÁNTICA te puede ayudar?<\br><\br>La sanación cuántica permite no solo sanar el cuerpo físico, sino también el cuerpo emocional y espiritual, donde residen traumas que dificultan el adecuado flujo de energía.<\br><\br>No solo identificar problemas energéticos relacionados con el hipertiroidismo, sino encontrar el origen energético y espiritual de dicha afección.<\br><\br>Hacerse consciente de que somos parte de un cuerpo energético desbloquea situaciones que nos afectan negativamente en diferentes áreas. <\br><\br>El ser humano está compuesto por tres cuerpos (el cuerpo físico, el cuerpo emocional o energético y el cuerpo espiritual) y que la enfermedad puede originarse en cualquiera de ellos. De cualquier forma, en el caso del hipertiroidismo observamos un exceso de energía que estimula a la glándula tiroides y le hace producir demasiada hormona tiroidea.<\br><\br>Como objetivo es encontrar la causa de tal exceso de energía y restaurar el equilibrio natural de todos los cuerpos de quien padece la enfermedad. Así, vemos también que la persona recupera sus propios recursos y comienza a estimular cambios en su vida, logrando el equilibrio que siempre ha deseado.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>#hipertiroidismo #terapiacuantica #medicinaintegrativa #bioneuroemocion #autoconocimiento #lnt | Tags: ['#hipertiroidismo', '#terapiacuantica', '#medicinaintegrativa', '#bioneuroemocion', '#autoconocimiento', '#lnt'] | Time Stamp: 1639943819

Post_ID: 2732037589984733421 | Post_Code: CXqJbaQDejt | Likes: 6 | Caption: Las Líneas Hartmann y las Líneas Curry son enrejados o cuadrículas, un patrón que siguen las energías telúricas (Hartmann) y cósmicas (Curry). Son distorsiones en las energías magnéticas de una zona, que pueden afectarnos. <\br><\br>"Conforme expuso el Dr. Hartmann, un nudo de Hartmann, donde se cruzan dos líneas de Hartmann o se combinan con cualquier otra perturbación, es el peor lugar para pasar mucho tiempo, trabajar o dormir, ya que la radiación nociva se intensifica en este lugar. <\br><\br>El Dr. Hartmann descubrió que la parte del cuerpo que se expone durante un largo período de tiempo a una radiación distorsionada es la ubicación del organismo donde comienza la enfermedad"<\br><\br>Así que es interesante conocer el mapa de esta rejilla en nuestra vivienda, e intentar que esos nudos NO coincidan con nuestra cama o nuestro sillón favorito. <\br><\br>La existencia de estas rejillas está muy debatida, por no existir aparato de medición aceptado... aunque dos radiestesistas con experiencia coincidirán en el la ubicación exacta del patrón con pocos centímetros de diferencia! <\br><\br>#trabajosenergeticos #limpiatucasa #lnt #energia #limpiezaenergetica #radiestesia | Tags: ['#trabajosenergeticos', '#limpiatucasa', '#lnt', '#energia', '#limpiezaenergetica', '#radiestesia'] | Time Stamp: 1639904281

Post_ID: 2731985246633286436 | Post_Code: CXp9httL1sk | Likes: 53 | Caption: Run into the Wonderland <\br>南二段 Day 6 ⛰️<\br><\br>前情提要：下雲峰後，待救者與消防隊一同搭直升機下山檢查，我與其他隊員一同走到拉庫音溪山屋過夜。<\br><\br>下到拉庫音溪時，聽見瀑布「嘩…嘩」的聲音，眼前晶瑩剔透的溪水實在太可口，直接衝去溪邊泡茶泡腳，很幸運的我們一群人包場，當大家窩在溫暖山屋內煮食，我則穿著短褲坐在外面，喝著茶吃著姐姐煮的牛肉冬粉 「天哪也太好吃了吧！」有菜有肉有愛，望著前方的霧氣懷抱著山巒翩翩起舞，此時黃喉貂探出頭來，用萌呆的模樣左探又探，聽到嚮導說「他會吃山羌！」兇猛的性格藏在這萌呆的外表之下，希望待會尿尿的時候不要對我的小祖宗怎麼樣，看看地圖嘉明湖就在不遠處了，此時才深深感受到「要回家了！」<\br><\br>Day 6<\br>拉庫音溪山屋-嘉明湖-三叉山⛰️-嘉明湖山屋-向陽山⛰️-向陽山屋-登山口<\br><\br>#Formosa#Taiwan#mountains#hiking#camping#backpacking#Trail#thruhiker#LNT#wonderland#HuangSolo#foundation#南二段 | Tags: ['#Formosa', '#Taiwan', '#mountains', '#hiking', '#camping', '#backpacking', '#Trail', '#thruhiker', '#LNT', '#wonderland', '#HuangSolo', '#foundation', '#南二段'] | Time Stamp: 1639898042
Post_ID: 2731978220511346287 | Post_Code: CXp77eHrr5v | Likes: 56 | Caption: Run into the Wonderland <\br>南二段 Day 5 ⛰️ 謝天謝地<\br><\br>前情提要：D4下午一點雲峰刀片岩發生山難。<\br>第一時間嚮導衝下80米溪谷尋找待救者，我在下午一點二十分抵達現場架設繩索另一名隊員下溪谷搜索，而後留在刀片岩協助搜索，高雄消防隊於下午一點三十分接獲通報整裝集結申請直昇機，於四點三十分抵達轆轆谷山屋，因天色已晚預定隔日一早上來搜索，小隊五名隊員則先前往轆轆山屋過夜，天色轉黑前嚮導帶著頭燈多次下溪谷搜索只找到待救者的登山杖、帽子、隨身小包，接著我於三叉路口搭設尖塔帳與嚮導留守。<\br><\br>事件發生後，真的深深感受到一個人的恐慌、絕望、無奈與責任感，雖然提供了協助，但在人命關天的情況下我還是感到愛莫能助，深感自身能力不足，無法提供更多協助，當下能做的只有聆聽與陪伴，隨著夜色模糊了週遭的群山，疲憊與憂傷劃開寧靜：「經過這一晚，一定沒救了。」，我們似乎已接受了一個生命逝去的事實，夜闌人靜時我們決定先行進入夢鄉，待明日支援抵達前進搜索。<\br><\br>這一夜除了寒風凜冽，心情也格外沈重，沒有真正入睡過，次日一早，帳內反潮的水滴落在臉頰，打開帳篷一看周圍雲霧繚繞，樹梢都化為雪白冰霜，而雲霧阻擋了訊號無法確定搜救隊ETA，領隊大哥：「你要不要去雲峰，現在早早出發還有時間。」心想好吧昨天都在刀片岩下方搜索，今天來去刀片岩上方看看會不會有收穫，便收拾技術裝備、急救包、糧食與水，踏上了雲峰之路，路過刀片岩時，閉上眼低下頭，「雖然素昧平生，但願你RIP 也讓我們帶你回家吧！」心中這樣想著，而後往雲峰邁進不時往溪谷望去，希望能找到蛛絲馬跡，接著奇蹟發生了，一個黑色褲子藍色上衣的人在前方草叢找路，身上毫無裝備，一問之下居然是待救者，我既興奮又擔心，趕緊請他坐下喝水吃東西並檢查傷勢，手腳顫抖，頭部撞傷，眼角血絲，判斷應該是低血糖、輕微失溫和腦震盪，接著大聲呼喊在營地的領隊，我們兩協助待救者通過刀片岩後，我繼續前往雲峰，站在高處握緊登山杖望向他們的背影，「謝天謝地。」<\br><\br>Day 5<\br>雲峰三叉路口-雲峰⛰️-雲峰三叉路口-雲峰下三叉營地-南雙頭山⛰️-拉庫音溪山屋<\br><\br>#Formosa#Taiwan#mountains#hiking#camping#backpacking#Trail#thruhiker#LNT#wonderland#HuangSolo#foundation#南二段 | Tags: ['#Formosa', '#Taiwan', '#mountains', '#hiking', '#camping', '#backpacking', '#Trail', '#thruhiker', '#LNT', '#wonderland', '#HuangSolo', '#foundation', '#南二段'] | Time Stamp: 1639897204

Post_ID: 2731650944967438149 | Post_Code: CXoxg_BJO9F | Likes: 8 | Caption: L U M B A R E S<\br><\br>La mayoría de las veces los motivos que dan lugar al dolor en la parte baja de la espalda son físicos, es decir, se producen a raíz de lesiones en las vértebras lumbares o los músculos o por una irritación en los nervios o las articulaciones, entre otras enfermedades:<\br><\br>⊙ Un reflejo de un daño muscular, como la presión prolongada en los músculos que sucede en un puesto de trabajo o, incluso, con el estrés.<\br><\br>⊙ Degeneración de los discos intervertebrales.<\br><\br>⊙ Hernia de disco.<\br><\br>⊙ Espondilolistesis.<\br><\br>⊙ La estenosis lumbar.<\br><\br>⊙ Osteoartritis<\br><\br>ꕥ EMOCIONES en el DOLOR de ESPALDA ꕥ<\br><\br>Cuando el dolor de espalda no se debe a causas físicas, como tensión acumulada o patologías más graves, el motivo del dolor lumbar puede estar en un CONFLICTO EMOCIONAL.<\br><\br>La espalda también puede verse afectada por el ESTRÉS, la FRUSTACIÓN, la IRA contenida y el RESENTIMIENTO. No obstante, la espalda representa a nivel emocional si nos sentimos o no respaldados por nuestro entorno. Es decir, los dolores de espalda suelen indicar una sensación de FALTA DE APOYO y según en la región en la que se produzcan, las causas y soluciones serán diferentes.<\br><\br>En el caso del DOLOR LUMBAR, observamos que este se debe a un temor a la pérdida económica, al desamparo financiero, y al miedo a no tener suficiente. Además, en estos casos la persona que padece dolor en las lumbares puede sentir que tiene que sobrevivir, pues existe un gran miedo a la falta de apoyo financiero.<\br><\br>En otras ocasiones, sin embargo, el DOLOR en la PARTE BAJA de la espalda está ocasionado por emociones enterradas o insatisfacción en el hogar.<\br><\br>Para estas situaciones, y debido a que el dolor tiene su origen en las emociones, puedes optar por recurrir a una terapia alternativa para las lumbares y tratar de transformar el miedo en poder personal.<\br><\br>El dolor de la espalda baja es cada vez más frecuente en nuestros días. Nuestros hábitos sedentarios y la inexpresión de las emociones se reflejan por medio de enfermedades que deben de ser comprendidas para un tratamiento adecuado. La TERAPIA CUÁNTICA es una terapia alternativa para lumbares no invasiva, con numerosos beneficios para el resto del cuerpo.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>#lumbares #lnt | Tags: ['#lumbares', '#lnt'] | Time Stamp: 1639858190

After hiking a while, I hear in the distance what sounds like a large group of coyotes howling. I'm unnerved given that I'm by myself but keep moving forward. When I get closer it's some sort of facility for huskies. I feel better knowing it's not wild animals. I meet a group of Colorado Trail hikers and we chat for a bit, and I realize I forgot one of my meals at Sasha's. Later in the day I get up to higher elevation and am completely surrounded by fog. I have to climb over a knifes edge ride (a ridge that has steep slopes on both sides) without being able to see more than maybe twenty feet in any direction. I also climb up a difficult hill I didn't need to by accident. At this point there's no discernable trail and I keep climbing up and down in vaguely the right direction, but the sunset looks amazing so there's that bit of levity. After the sun sets I find a road, which is great because it's easy to follow and my phone is low on batteries. Around 9:45pm-ish I get to a sketchy spot about a mile before the spot we picked out to camp next to water. My headlamp died a little bit ago, so I decide to stop there with no water. Worth noting, I've been by myself pretty much all day and at this point I don't know where any of my companions are, so I'm even more skeeved out about camping at elevation with less than ideal weather. Your gravity and the beautiful ones in it. <\br><\br>Be kind to them all.<\br><\br>They deserve it.<\br><\br>#hotspringz #SoulfulSoakSociety<\br><\br>#frozen #blue #utah #hot #utahhotsprings #steamseekers #warmth #onsen  #utahisrad #wowutah #utahunique #beautahful #source #antiinflammatory #warmandwet  #lnt #getoutside #utahhyes #utahphotography #packitout #love #connection #mountainlife | Tags: ['#hotspringz', '#SoulfulSoakSociety', '#frozen', '#blue', '#utah', '#hot', '#utahhotsprings', '#steamseekers', '#warmth', '#onsen', '#utahisrad', '#wowutah', '#utahunique', '#beautahful', '#source', '#antiinflammatory', '#warmandwet', '#lnt', '#getoutside', '#utahhyes', '#utahphotography', '#packitout', '#love', '#connection', '#mountainlife'] | Time Stamp: 1639785304

Post_ID: 2730467611884576080 | Post_Code: CXkkdONFt1Q | Likes: 23 | Caption: 應該是舊制度下最後一班3級山藝，如果你想完成三級後直接註冊山藝領袖，呢個應該是最後機會…<\br><\br>三級山藝訓練課程 (MCLVIII_2021Dec)<\br><\br>看見疫情，不時提的我們要健康，登山是好活動，但看到每星期日過後既山林，也不禁心痛！我們可以無痕地與大自然共處嗎？共存共享是態度，不是消費，作為山藝領袖更應清楚。<\br><\br>『登山的原因，就是因為山在那裡！』 我們希望每一位登山人都能在山上享受大自然與人的共存，登山最重要不是技術，是態度。當然我也希望將自己擁有的技術同大家分享， 我們堅持將登山中不同技術（攀登，攀岩，雪山經驗）整合及研究，令學員能帶領隊員去面對不同困難地形，這就是我們三級的目標！<\br><\br>本課程按照香港攀山總會山藝訓練計劃中三級山藝及助教課程編制，課程包括4次課堂講學及4次2日1夜之戶外實習訓練。<\br><\br>課程內容包括：<\br>不留痕跡登山(Leave No Trace)理念的實行<\br>衣著及裝備<\br>地圖閱讀<\br>指南針運用<\br>全球衛星定位儀 (GPS)<\br>旅程策劃<\br>繩結的認識及正確的應用<\br>繩索運用及防護技巧<\br>山野安全<\br>各種惡劣天氣現象形成的簡介<\br>講學/解說技巧<\br>領袖才能<\br><\br>入學資格：年滿18歲或以上之人士及持有香港攀山總會二級山藝證書或同等資歷<\br><\br>理論課日期：22/12 Wed(可協調另一天）, 7/1 Fri,  25/1 Tue, 9/2 Wed<\br>4個3小時理論<\br>理論課時間：19:00-22:00<\br>理論課地點：荃灣<\br><\br>實習課日期：<\br>實習營<\br>1. 導航營 15-16/1 , 1800-1800（黑夜導航技術，生命支援技術及創傷處理 I）<\br>2. 營藝營 22-23/1, 1800-1800（困難環境露營及生存技巧，生命支援技術及創傷處理 II）<\br>3. 繩索營 11-12/2 1900-1900（繩索於登山技術中應用，游繩，飛索，渡河技術）<\br>4. 穿林營 25-26/2 1900-1900（於密林環境中如何導航及前進，BIVY露宿技術，傷者搬運）<\br><\br>導師：香港攀山總會二級山藝教練(茶包)<\br><\br>#山藝 #攀岩 #運動攀登 #潛水 #歷奇 #xsport #香港人 #香港本土教練 #行山 #爬石 #一級山藝 #二級山藝 #一級攀登 #二級攀登 #一級攀岩 #三級山藝 #infiniTea #Adventure #photograpy <\br>#Diving #LNT #山藝領袖 | Tags: ['#山藝', '#攀岩', '#運動攀登', '#潛水', '#歷奇', '#xsport', '#香港人', '#香港本土教練', '#行山', '#爬石', '#一級山藝', '#二級山藝', '#一級攀登', '#二級攀登', '#一級攀岩', '#三級山藝', '#infiniTea', '#Adventure', '#photograpy', '#Diving', '#LNT', '#山藝領袖'] | Time Stamp: 1639717125

Post_ID: 2730425684759713290 | Post_Code: CXka7GhtJYK | Likes: 406 | Caption: "LEAVE NO TRACE"ダメージを残さず、自然を残そう🌳<\br><\br>LNT原則6：野生動物の尊重<\br><\br>シリーズでご紹介しているLeave No Trace（LNT）は、ダメージを残さずに自然を楽しむための環境配慮のテクニック 。今日、ご紹介するのは＜LNT 原則6 ：野生動物の尊重＞です。<\br><\br>野生動物は、距離をとって、彼らの自然な生き生きとした姿を楽しみましょう。不適切な距離は、野生動物が警戒したり、逃げたり、時には攻撃されることもあります。十分な距離をとって野生動物を観察し、動物に広い生息域を与え、食料を動物から隔離し、食べものや食べかすを持ち帰ることで、野生動物は生き生きとした姿を見せてくれます。<\br><\br>━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━<\br><\br>➤KEEN BLOG<\br>https://lnky.jp/eHtX6xN<\br><\br>＊プロフィールURLからKEEN BLOGを参照ください。<\br><\br>━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━<\br><\br>KEENが、LNTを応援するのは、次の世代にも、この素晴らしい自然を楽しんでもらいたいから。一人一人の思いやりのある行動が、自然へのダメージを最小限にしていきます。ぜひこのLNTの7つの原則を思い出して、ダメージを残さず、自然を楽しみ、次世代にも自然のバトンをつないでいきましょう。ぜひ、一緒に。<\br><\br>#KEEN #KEENEFFECT #OUTSIDEBETTER #LeaveNoTrace #LNT #SDGs #持続可能性 #環境へのインパクトを最小限に<\br><\br>@LNTJAPAN | Tags: ['#KEEN', '#KEENEFFECT', '#OUTSIDEBETTER', '#LeaveNoTrace', '#LNT', '#SDGs', '#持続可能性', '#環境へのインパクトを最小限に'] | Time Stamp: 1639712127

Follow the park on Twitter & turn on notifications to get notified the instant it opens & closes!<\br><\br>• The middle of the day is the warmest & busiest part of the day. My advice is never to plan an elopement or wedding in Arches National Park during the middle of the day.<\br><\br>• If you have any guests, be sure they carpool & be sure the cars are full of passengers; I cannot emphasize this enough, parking is minimal. Post_ID: 2729659372668107741 | Post_Code: CXhsryxsrvd | Likes: 135 | Caption: As seasons change, so do our practices to stay safe outside and to protect the places where we play! <\br><\br>In the winter, the environment changes quickly and access points may be more limited. It may not be cold or snowing close to home, but that could change quickly as you venture out.<\br><\br>Do you know best practices for #winterhiking and other outdoor adventures?<\br><\br>We teamed up with @recreate.responsibly to share the #RecreateResponsibly Winter Edition Guidelines: <\br><\br>❄️ Know Before You Go - Some areas are seasonally closed or have limited hours, and many places become dangerous with winter weather. Research your destination, weather, and road conditions prior to your trip. <\br><\br>❄️ Plan and Prepare - Know your limits and your gear. Pack extra layers, waterproof clothing, and safety equipment or beacons for the backcountry. Have a Plan B in case you can’t access your destination. <\br><\br>❄️ Build an Inclusive Outdoors - Everyone deserves to experience a winter wonderland. Be an active part of making the outdoors safe, accessible, and welcoming for all identities and abilities. <\br><\br>❄️ Respect Others - From mountain tops to shores to prairies, parking can be in short supply in the winter. Park only in safe and legal spaces. Learn to Ski Kind or Tread Lightly when skiing, riding, or traversing off-road. <\br><\br>❄️ Leave No Trace - Respect the land, water, wildlife, and Indigenous communities. Follow the Leave No Trace Winter Use Principles. <\br><\br>❄️ Make it Better - Keep our winter playgrounds clean. Pack out any human or pet waste. Consider your responsibility to take action to protect our climate--today’s snow is tomorrow’s water.<\br><\br>How are you recreating responsibly this winter?<\br><\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br><\br>#52hikechallenge #52hikechallenge2021 #52hikechallenge2022 #52hikes #hikingchallenge #winterhike #winterhikes #coldweatherhiking #hikingcommunity #hikingculture #hikinglifestyle #hikingvibes #hikinglife #werehikers #hikersofinstagram #hikeitoff #hikeon #hikemoreworryless #idhikethat #whyihike #leavenotrace #lnt #diversifyoutdoors #inclusivityoutdoors | Tags: ['#winterhiking', '#RecreateResponsibly', '#52hikechallenge', '#52hikechallenge2021', '#52hikechallenge2022', '#52hikes', '#hikingchallenge', '#winterhike', '#winterhikes', '#coldweatherhiking', '#hikingcommunity', '#hikingculture', '#hikinglifestyle', '#hikingvibes', '#hikinglife', '#werehikers', '#hikersofinstagram', '#hikeitoff', '#hikeon', '#hikemoreworryless', '#idhikethat', '#whyihike', '#leavenotrace', '#lnt', '#diversifyoutdoors', '#inclusivityoutdoors'] | Time Stamp: 1639620776

Post_ID: 2729533878035915690 | Post_Code: CXhQJmyuaOq | Likes: 58 | Caption: Sign up for a guided mountain hike with Friends of Panola Mountain State Park to visit the conservation area - aka to hike on Panola Mountain itself. Carefully protected from most foot traffic to preserve the pristine rock outcrop ecosystem, Panola Mountain is an ecological treasure that can only be visited with a guide. Sign up by calling the Nature Center at (770) 389-7801.<\br>.<\br>Throughout the American Southeast, not many large, pristine rock outcrops remain. Two of the other local rock outcrops, or "monadnocks," Arabia Mountain and Stone Mountain, have both been heavily quarried and impacted by humans, for example. A similar fate has fallen many of the other monadnocks in the Southeast. At Panola Mountain, however, the story is different. Because the rock itself is no good for quarrying (the granite formation has a more brittle stone that cracks and splinters when broken). Luckily for us, that means that Panola Mountain has remained relatively untouched, with a pristine ecosystem that looks much as it has for thousands of years.<\br>Above: a guided hike on Panola Mountain.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>.<\br>#ArabiaMountainNationalHeritageArea #ArabiaMountain #PanolaMountain #NationalHeritageArea#NationalPark #NationalHistoricSite #StatePark #GAStateParks #GeorgiaStatePark #Parks #Hiking #HikeLife #WanderNorthGA #AtlantaTrails #RespectThePark #LeaveNoTrace #OptOutside #RecreateResponsibly #LNT | Tags: ['#ArabiaMountainNationalHeritageArea', '#ArabiaMountain', '#PanolaMountain', '#NationalHeritageArea', '#NationalPark', '#NationalHistoricSite', '#StatePark', '#GAStateParks', '#GeorgiaStatePark', '#Parks', '#Hiking', '#HikeLife', '#WanderNorthGA', '#AtlantaTrails', '#RespectThePark', '#LeaveNoTrace', '#OptOutside', '#RecreateResponsibly', '#LNT'] | Time Stamp: 1639605816

Se trata de abrir tu mente, de abrir tu cuerpo y sobretodo de abrir la escucha hacia tu alma. Porque en la vida tenemos  que observar lo que vemos, tenemos que escuchar lo que oímos, tenemos que hacer caso a nuestra intuición, que es nuestra más sabía consejera.<\br><\br>Porque si no el 90% de las veces no haríamos nada, perderíamos oportunidades constantemente, perderíamos aprendizajes y vivencias maravillosas. Porque a veces hay que tirarse un poco al vacío y confiar, confiar porque todo se dará de la mejor manera. <\br><\br>✨ Las que más imposibles parecen muchas veces acaban siendo las mejores oportunidades ✨<\br><\br>✨ Los sueños más grandes empiezan con los pasos más pequeños ✨<\br><\br>✨ Las mejores carcajadas empiezan con las más tímidas de las sonrisas ✨<\br><\br>✨ No te pierdas la vida, vive la vida y seguirá dándote más motivos para vivir ✨<\br><\br>✨ Si sueñas, paga el precio luchando por ello, hasta que a la vida no le quede más remedio que dártelo ✨<\br><\br>✨ Los sueños se hacen realidad, abre tus sentidos, y aprovecha las oportunidades ✨<\br><\br>🤍 Deja que la magia actúe <\br>Y verás de todo <\br>Lo que eres capaz 🤍<\br><\br>🤍 Gracias, te amo 🤍<\br><\br>#hooponopono #frasesinstagram #frasesinspiradoras #frasesmotivadoras #instablog #instagood #metodoschwiderski #metodoatlante #lnt #terapia #terapeutacapacitadolnt® #terapiacuantica #terapias #reiki #tameana #registrosakáshicos #registrosakashicos #tarot #amor #amorpropio #oportunidades #vida #love #loveyourself #life #lifestyle  #sanacioncuantica #sanacionfisica #sanacionespiritual #sanacionemocional | Tags: ['#hooponopono', '#frasesinstagram', '#frasesinspiradoras', '#frasesmotivadoras', '#instablog', '#instagood', '#metodoschwiderski', '#metodoatlante', '#lnt', '#terapia', '#terapeutacapacitadolnt®', '#terapiacuantica', '#terapias', '#reiki', '#tameana', '#registrosakáshicos', '#registrosakashicos', '#tarot', '#amor', '#amorpropio', '#oportunidades', '#vida', '#love', '#loveyourself', '#life', '#lifestyle', '#sanacioncuantica', '#sanacionfisica', '#sanacionespiritual', '#sanacionemocional'] | Time Stamp: 1639587303

As we head into the weekend and the upcoming holiday break, when visitors to Zion will increase, please remember to follow these Leave No Trace best practices.<\br><\br>1. Tag Thoughtfully<\br>Avoid geotags or hashtags that point out specific locations. Instead, use general locations, states or even regions.<\br><\br>2. Be Mindful of What Your Images Portray<\br>Don’t show yourself in places you shouldn’t be, and don’t reveal remote locations.<\br><\br>3. Give Back to the Places You Love<\br>Pack in, pack out and leave a place better than you found it.<\br> <\br>4. Encourage and Inspire #LNT in Social Media Posts<\br>Raising awareness is the number one way to educate others about Leave No Trace. When sharing America’s amazing outdoor spaces on social media, be sure to also share the Leave No Trace message.<\br><\br>As a reminder, the 7 Leave No Trace principles are:<\br>1. Plan ahead and prepare<\br>2. Travel and camp on durable surfaces<\br>3. Dispose of waste properly<\br>4. Leave what you find<\br>5. Minimize campfire impacts<\br>6. Respect wildlife<\br>7. So today we are going to talk about liquids disposal. 💧<\br>Disposing of your liquids depends on where you are. Post_ID: 2728680120518777647 | Post_Code: CXeOBzJMRsv | Likes: 18 | Caption: Terapia Alternativa para la depresión. <\br>La depresión forma parte de las afecciones más habituales en nuestros días. Incapacitante y silenciosa, esta enfermedad requiere de una atención temprana. Junto a la psicoterapia y la medicación, recuerda que puedes escoger una terapia alternativa para la depresión que te facilite la conexión con tu interior y te ofrezca una perspectiva más completa.<\br><\br>Qué es la depresión<\br>La depresión es un trastorno del ánimo que causa un profundo sentimiento de tristeza y desmotivación. A través de este, la persona que se ve afectada pierde el interés en realizar tareas cotidianas e, incluso, aquellas actividades que con anterioridad disfrutaba.<\br>Desde un punto de vista espiritual, la depresión puede originarse debido a un trauma emocional que afecta a la capacidad del globo energético de regular la energía o, incluso, a conflictos kármicos que están aún por resolver. Según el enfoque, se recomendará psicoterapia y medicamentos o una terapia alternativa para la depresión.<\br><\br>LA NUEVA TERAPIA<\br>La Nueva Terapia o LNT es un sistema de sanación cuántico canalizado por el osteópata y enfermero Philippe Schwiderski. Esta terapia considera que son los traumas emocionales y kármicos aquellos que influyen directamente en la salud del ser humano. Para abordar estos conflictos, la LNT recurre al Despertar de la Energía y a los Tres Ejes de Sanación para llevar a cabo la autosanación y la sanación de quien padece la enfermedad.<\br><\br>Explorar el estado del globo energético, la apertura de las antenas energéticas que forman parte del cuerpo, los bloqueos de energía y las posibles fisuras son tan solo algunos de los pasos para tratar la depresión desde La Nueva Terapia.<\br><\br>#terapiacuantica #lnt #lanuevaterapiabarcelona #lanuevaterapia #gururaskaur #tierracrecimientopersonal<\br>#santacolomadegramenet | Tags: ['#terapiacuantica', '#lnt', '#lanuevaterapiabarcelona', '#lanuevaterapia', '#gururaskaur', '#tierracrecimientopersonal', '#santacolomadegramenet'] | Time Stamp: 1639504040
Post_ID: 2728655551543416569 | Post_Code: CXeIcRgJJb5 | Likes: 59 | Caption: ***Dolly Sods designated as LNT “Hot Spot.”***<\br>•<\br>•<\br>The Leave No Trace (LNT) organization has announced that the Dolly Sods Wilderness has been designated as one of its 2022 Hot Spots, and will devote special attention and resources to the impacts which threaten its natural character. There has been a steady rise in visitation at Dolly Sods over the past decade, with a significant spike during the pandemic. This had led to significant impact on and degradation of the wilderness character of Dolly Sods. The LNT organization will coordinate with the Monongahela National Forest and WVHC’s Dolly Sods Wilderness Stewards to plan training, workshops and community events to address specific issues related to the effects of high visitor use. These include the proliferation and impact of campsites, vegetation loss, and appropriate backcountry practices. We will share more information and announcements of events as plans develop. Please check our website to learn more about our Wilderness Stewards program and find out how you can help. Post_ID: 2728580766430997761 | Post_Code: CXd3cAcFS0B | Likes: 42 | Caption: A mysterious field full of what appears to be satellite dishes are searching the skies in the Eastern Sierra. The Owens Valley Radio Observatory is just outside of Bishop, California in the little town of Big Pine, and the satellite dishes are actually radio telescopes and antennas. The Owens Valley Radio Observatory is one of the largest university-operated radio observatories in the world. There are a number of different research projects going on at OVRO, home to more than a dozen radio telescopes and even more antennas. A lot of what goes on here is highly technical and not that visual. These telescope dishes record radio waves that are processed in complex computers, then converted into data that only scientists can read. The telescopes were built in the Owens Valley because it has clear skies and is far away from radio electrical interference. Essentially, it's in the middle of nowhere. The telescopes come in all shapes and sizes and search all sorts of things. The largest dish is 40-meters, and it studies black holes. A series of medium dishes locate Fast Radio Bursts and small ground level antenna looking devices study something referred to as red shifts.⁠<\br>#Caltech @owensvalley @easternsierra @bigears⁠<\br>⁠<\br>#travelgram #instatravel #adventure #explore #photooftheday #nature #vacation #traveling #instadaily #bartellsbackroads #abc10tv #pitstop #roadsideattraction #california #norcal #socal #morningblend #LNT #DronesOfCalifornia #roadtrip #californiahistoricallandmark #californiadreaming #californialove⁠ | Tags: ['#Caltech', '#travelgram', '#instatravel', '#adventure', '#explore', '#photooftheday', '#nature', '#vacation', '#traveling', '#instadaily', '#bartellsbackroads', '#abc10tv', '#pitstop', '#roadsideattraction', '#california', '#norcal', '#socal', '#morningblend', '#LNT', '#DronesOfCalifornia', '#roadtrip', '#californiahistoricallandmark', '#californiadreaming', '#californialove\u2060'] | Time Stamp: 1639492196
